                            <comment id="17740805" author="brandon.williams" created="Thu, 6 Jul 2023 21:03:51 +0000"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m fighting with an issue this upgrade solves&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;

&lt;p&gt;To clarify, the problem was &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/commit/00cf31882beaf5e28dc600489f9ea8b69d1803df&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;, but I couldn&apos;t find it until I upgraded owasp and it gave me a meaningful error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3.0 needs the suppressions we added in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-17966&quot; title=&quot;jackson-databind vulnerability CVE-2022-42003 CVE-2022-42004&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;CASSANDRA-17966&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;CASSANDRA-17966&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; (I found it odd that it didn&apos;t complain about 3.0 there, so I feel good about this upgrade.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It and 3.11 both need the libthrift suppressions copied to the thinkaurelis disruptor server (but you can&apos;t remove the libthrift suppressions, you need both.)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4.0, 4.1, and trunk just work.&lt;/p&gt;

